04/11/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, the chairman-in-office of the OSCE, met with NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer in Brussels on Wednesday (3 November).
They discussed co-operation between the two organisations, as well as the preparations for the upcoming OSCE ministerial meeting in Sofia.
In other news Wednesday, Bulgarian Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov announced that Bulgarian troops in Iraq would be downsized by around 10 per cent, to 430, next month.
He explained that the reduction was due to a change in expected duties, following the contingent's relocation to Al Diwaniyah.
(Dnevnik - 04/11/04;
NATO Web site, bTV, Bulgarian National Radio - 03/11/04)
